---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Late Payment Calculator — Late Fees & Interest | latepaycalc.com';
const description = 'Free late payment calculator. Estimate late fees, interest on overdue invoices, and statutory late-payment penalties under state law. Covers both B2B invoices and employment final-paycheck rules.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Late Payment Calculator</h1>
  <p>Calculate what you're owed on a late invoice or paycheck. This calculator covers both B2B late-fee scenarios (overdue customer invoices, contract late-payment clauses) and US employment final-paycheck penalties.</p>

  <section aria-labelledby="calc-heading">
    <h2 id="calc-heading">Calculate late payment</h2>
    <noscript>
      <p><strong>Note:</strong> the interactive calculator requires JavaScript. Manual formula for invoice late fees: <code>Late fee = Amount overdue &times; (Annual interest rate &divide; 365) &times; Days late</code> if your contract specifies an interest rate.</p>
    </noscript>
    <div id="calculator-island">
      <form class="calc-form" data-pilot-placeholder>
        <label>Amount owed (USD) <input type="number" min="0" step="0.01" placeholder="5000" /></label>
        <label>Days overdue <input type="number" min="0" step="1" placeholder="30" /></label>
        <label>Annual late-payment interest rate (%) <input type="number" min="0" step="0.5" placeholder="8" /></label>
        <label>Late fee (flat, if contract specifies) (USD) <input type="number" min="0" step="0.01" placeholder="50" /></label>
        <label>Type <select><option>B2B invoice / contract</option><option>Employment final paycheck</option></select></label>
        <button type="button">Calculate (interactive version loads with JS)</button>
      </form>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How late-payment calculations work</h2>
    <p>Late-payment math depends on what your contract or law says. The most common methods:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Flat late fee.</strong> A fixed dollar amount imposed when payment is overdue. Common in service contracts. Example: "$50 late fee if invoice is more than 30 days past due."</li>
      <li><strong>Interest on overdue balance.</strong> An annual interest rate applied to the unpaid amount, accruing daily until paid. Example: 8% APR on a $5,000 invoice 30 days late = $5,000 &times; (0.08 &divide; 365) &times; 30 = $32.88.</li>
      <li><strong>Statutory late penalty.</strong> Imposed by state law for specific situations (e.g., final paychecks in many states). Often a multiple of daily wages.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Some contracts combine methods. See our <a href="/methodology">methodology</a> for full formula details.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>B2B invoice late fees</h2>
    <p>For overdue customer invoices, your right to a late fee depends on what your contract or invoice terms say. If your contract specifies a late fee or interest rate, that's typically what applies. If it doesn't, many states allow you to charge "reasonable" interest at the statutory rate (often 4&ndash;10% per year depending on the state) for commercial debts.</p>
    <p>You can't usually charge surprise late fees after the fact. State usury laws cap how high a contractual rate can go.</p>
    <p>For deeper coverage: <a href="/guides/how-late-pay-penalties-are-calculated">How late-pay penalties are calculated</a>.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Employment final paycheck penalties</h2>
    <p>If you're an employee whose final paycheck was paid late, state law often provides specific penalties &mdash; sometimes severe. In California for example, the "waiting time penalty" is one full day's wages for each day the final paycheck is late, up to 30 days.</p>
    <p>Final-paycheck deadlines also vary by state and termination type. See <a href="/guides/final-paycheck-deadlines-by-state">Final paycheck deadlines by state</a>.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Recent guides</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/guides/how-late-pay-penalties-are-calculated">How late-pay penalties are calculated</a></li>
      <li><a href="/guides/final-paycheck-deadlines-by-state">Final paycheck deadlines by state</a></li>
      <li><a href="/guides/what-to-do-if-paid-late">What to do if you're paid late</a></li>
      <li><a href="/guides/common-late-pay-misconceptions">Common late-pay misconceptions</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <style>
    .calc-form { display:grid;gap:0.75rem;max-width:480px;margin:1rem 0; }
    .calc-form label { display:grid;gap:0.25rem;font-size:0.95rem; }
    .calc-form input, .calc-form select { padding:0.5rem;font-size:1rem;border:1px solid var(--color-border);border-radius:4px; }
    .calc-form button { padding:0.6rem 1rem;background:var(--color-accent);color:white;border:none;border-radius:4px;cursor:pointer;font-size:1rem; }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
